152 (c) The authority may create subcommittees as it deems appropriate. The authority may
153 appoint as members of the subcommittees such individuals from the community as the
154 authority deems appropriate, and such members do not have to be members of the
155 authority. The subcommittees shall serve in an advisory capacity to the authority. The
156 chairperson of the authority shall choose from among the members of each subcommittee
157 a person to serve as chairperson of that subcommittee. The chairpersons of the
158 subcommittees shall serve four-year terms and shall be eligible for reappointment.
159 (d) A majority of the members of the authority shall constitute a quorum. No vacancy on
160 the authority shall impair the right of the quorum to exercise all of the rights and perform
161 all of the duties of the authority.
162 (e) A vacancy on the authority shall exist in the office of any member of the authority who
163 is convicted of a felony or who enters a plea of nolo contendere thereto; who is convicted
164 of a crime involving moral turpitude or who enters a plea of nolo contendere thereto; who
165 is convicted of any act of misfeasance, malfeasance, or nonfeasance of such person's duties
166 as a member of the authority; or who fails to attend three consecutive regular meetings of
167 the authority without an excuse approved by a resolution of the authority.
168 (f) All meetings of the authority, regular or special, shall be open to the public.
169 (g) No member or employee of the authority shall have, directly or indirectly, any financial
170 interest, profit, or benefit in any contract, work, or business of the authority nor in the sale,
171 lease, or purchase of any property to or from the authority.
