256 (a) Each year the authority shall have made an independent audit and examination of the
257 authority's financial records and transactions. Such audit shall be made in accordance with
258 established national audit and accounting standards. Such audit shall be made on or before
259 the one hundred-eightieth day following the end of the authority's fiscal year. Copies of
260 such audit shall be available for public review and provided to the state auditor.
261 (b) Annual audit reports of the authority shall contain at least:
262 (1) Financial statements prepared in conformity with generally accepted national
263 accounting principles, setting forth the financial condition and results of operation of each
264 fund and activity of the authority; and
265 (2) The opinion of the performing auditor with respect to the financial statement in
266 addition to an explanation of any qualification or disclaimers contained in the opinion.
267 Such opinion shall also disclose, in accordance with generally accepted national auditing
268 standards, any apparent or material violation of state law discovered during the audit.
269 (c) The authority shall forward to the state auditor written comments on the findings and
270 recommendations in the report, including a plan for corrective action taken or planned and
271 comments on the status of the corrective action taken on prior findings.
272 (d) The state auditor shall review the audit report and written comments submitted to the
273 auditor's office to ensure that it conforms with generally accepted national auditing
